fRateLimiter[T]**: Meta-limiter that applies multiple rate limiters and returns the maximum delay from any of them.\n\n**Controller Reconcile Loop Pattern:**\n\nControllers in kubernetes repository (deployment, job, daemon, cronjob, etc.) implement the standard reconcile pattern:\n\n1. **Initialization**: Controllers create a TypedRateLimitingInterface using NewTypedRateLimitingQueueWithConfig with DefaultTypedControllerRateLimiter.\n\n2. **Queue Population**: Event handlers call enqueue() to add items via queue.Add() for immediate processing, or enqueueRateLimited() to use AddRateLimited() for items needing retry.\n\n3. **Worker Loop**: The worker(ctx) method spawns multiple goroutines that call processNextWorkItem():\n   ```\n   func (c *Controller) processNextWorkItem(ctx) bool {\n       key, quit := c.queue.Get()  // Blocks until item available\n       if quit { return false }\n       defer c.queue.Done(key)     // Mark item as processed\n       \n       err := c.syncHandler(ctx, key)  // Reconciliation logic\n       c.handleErr(err, key)           // Error handling\n       return true\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Error Handling**: The handleErr() function implements retry logic:\n   - On success: queue.Forget(key) to clear failure tracking\n   - On retriable error: if NumRequeues(key) < maxRetries, call queue.AddRateLimited(key)\n   - On permanent error: log and forget after max retries exceeded\n\nThis architecture ensures fair processing (FIFO), prevents concurrent processing of the same item, supports multiple workers, and implements exponential backoff retry with token bucket rate limiting for production-grade controller operation."
